cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the modification of a compiler to incorporate a new intermediate representation (IR) for parallelism. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on improving the performance of machine learning applications through compiler optimizations. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the performance improvements achieved on different CPU architectures. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses parallelism and optimizations for parallel computation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses modifications to a software tool (the XLA compiler in TensorFlow) to improve its performance.
